body:
### Describe the bug

Having a scheduled method using quartz. When we get the previous/next firetimes of that job  using `io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduler` they never get updated as they should when the job runs.

### Expected behavior

Firetimes gets updated to the right values of the previous execution and the next execution

### Actual behavior

Values are not getting updated;

```
2022-05-24 20:49:34,894 INFO  [org.acm.GreetingResource] (QuarkusQuartzScheduler_Worker-2) Previous Fire time is: null
2022-05-24 20:49:34,896 INFO  [org.acm.GreetingResource] (QuarkusQuartzScheduler_Worker-2) Next Fire time is: 2022-05-25T00:49:24.893Z
2022-05-24 20:49:44,894 INFO  [org.acm.GreetingResource] (QuarkusQuartzScheduler_Worker-3) Previous Fire time is: null
2022-05-24 20:49:44,895 INFO  [org.acm.GreetingResource] (QuarkusQuartzScheduler_Worker-3) Next Fire time is: 2022-05-25T00:49:24.893Z
```

### How to Reproduce?

Reproducer: https://github.com/manofthepeace/quarkus-quartz-firetimes

Steps to reproduce;
1. run the app with mvn quarkus:dev
2. look at the logs

### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`

Darwin Kernel Version 21.4.0

### Output of `java -version`

OpenJDK Runtime Environment Temurin-17.0.3+7 (build 17.0.3+7)

### GraalVM version (if different from Java)

_No response_

### Quarkus version or git rev

2.9.1

### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)

maven 3.8.5

### Additional information

Actual code;

```java
    @Inject
    Scheduler scheduler;

    @Inject
    Logger log;

    @Scheduled(every = "10s", identity = "test")
    public void hello() {
        Instant pft = scheduler.getScheduledJob("test").getPreviousFireTime();
        Instant nft = scheduler.getScheduledJob("test").getNextFireTime();
        log.infof("Previous Fire time is: %s", pft);
        log.infof("Next Fire time is: %s", nft);
    }
```
